				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$p < 0.05$$\end{document}p<0.05) was established between the changes in modified RECIST and computed tumour volume.

In view of the challenging nature of automated MPM segmentation, Frauenfelder et al. [10] applied interpolation to hand-drawn tumour contours found on every 4–5 axial cuts. Inter-observer agreement of the segmented tumour was reported to be significantly higher than that of modified RECIST (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
